	<page name="About" title="EntropyDrivenStudios | About" heading="About">
		<div id='aboutScroll'>
			<div class="scrollbar"><div class="track"><div class="thumb"><div class="end"></div></div></div></div>
			<div align="center" class="viewport">
			<div align="center" class="overview">
				<span class="auhdtxt">Who are we?</span>
				<p class="intxt">We are I. I am a student studying Computational Astrophysics, who just happens to be interested in 3D design, artwork and animation. And on the computational side, I am interested in graphic programing, and indi game development.</p>
				<span class="auhdtxt">What do we do?</span>
				<p class="intxt">I create digital artwork both still and animation, from computer generated and post produced compositions, as well as graphical programs (games). This artwork can be original, subject based, or fan based, and is done in my spare time.</p>
				<span class="auhdtxt">Why do we do this?</span>
				<p class="intxt">Why do anything that takes time and effort? For fun of course!</p>
				<span class="auhdtxt">This is really bugging me, your "Stellar Explosion" is wrong...</span>
				<p class="intxt">As an Astrophysicist, I realize this. However, you have to admit, it does look pretty cool!</p>
				<span class="auhdtxt">What programs do you use?</span>
				<p class="intxt">For post work, and textures, I use Adobe Photoshop. For modeling and rendering, Autodesk 3DS Max. And for programing and compiling Visual Studio, or an Emacs window and g++.</p>
				<span class="auhdtxt">You said that you do computational stuff, what languages do you know?</span>
				<p class="intxt">I am fluent in: C/C++, FORTRAN, C-Shell, Bash, IDL, Python, and HTML / CSS (How I wrote this website). I do graphical programing with OpenGL (SDL), and GLSL.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		</div>	
